subject_pheno <- fread("/scratch/st-dennisjk-1/wcasazza/RICHS_genotyping/RICHS_Subject_phenotypes.GRU.txt")
sample_attr <-fread("/scratch/st-dennisjk-1/wcasazza/RICHS_genotyping/RICHS_Sample_Attributes.GRU.txt")
sample_multi <- fread("/scratch/st-dennisjk-1/wcasazza/RICHS_genotyping/RICHS_Sample.MULTI.txt")
subject_multi <- fread("/scratch/st-dennisjk-1/wcasazza/RICHS_genotyping/RICHS_Subject.MULTI.txt")
fam <- read.delim("/scratch/st-dennisjk-1/wcasazza/RICHS_genotyping/phg001102.v1.RICHS.genotype-calls-matrixfmt.MEGA_Consortium.c1.GRU/plink_for_dbgap.fam",header=FALSE,sep="")
combined_meta <- subject_pheno %>%
    left_join(
        sample_multi
    )
Joining, by = c("dbGaP_Subject_ID", "SUBJECT_ID")
fam %>%
    left_join(
        combined_meta,
        by = c("V2"="SAMPLE_ID")
    ) %>%
    select(V1,V2,maternal_ethnicity) %>%
    group_by(maternal_ethnicity) %>%
    summarize(n())
`summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)

    ) %>%
    group_by(V5) %>%
    summarize(n())

Plot Fhet within Cluster

Plotting \(F_{het}\) within each reported ethnicity:

clst <- fread(paste0(BASE_DIR,"raw_data.clst"))
fhet_data <- fread(paste0(BASE_DIR,"raw_data.geno.maf.mind.sex_check.het"))
fhet_data %>%
    left_join(clst,by=c("IID"="V2")) %>%
    mutate(maternal_ethnicity=V3) %>%
    ggplot(aes(F,fill=maternal_ethnicity)) + geom_histogram(bins=30)

plot_pcs <- function(dat,pc_col1,pc_col2,pc,what,color="maternal_ethnicity"){
    p1 <- dat %>%
      inner_join(combined_meta,by = c("V2"="SAMPLE_ID")) %>%
      mutate(maternal_ethnicity= as.factor(maternal_ethnicity)) %>%
      ggplot(aes_string(pc_col1,pc_col2,color=color)) +
        geom_point() +
        labs(x=sprintf("PC%d",pc),y=sprintf("PC%d",pc+1)) +
        theme_minimal()
    p2 <- dat %>%
      inner_join(combined_meta,by = c("V2"="SAMPLE_ID")) %>%
      mutate(maternal_ethnicity= as.factor(maternal_ethnicity)) %>%
      ggplot(aes_string(pc_col1,"age",color=color)) +
        geom_point() +
        labs(x=sprintf("PC%d",pc)) +
        ggtitle("PCA RICHS vs. Age") +
        theme_minimal()
    if(what != ""){
        print(p2)
    }else{
        print(p1)
    }
}

assigned_ancestry

The above looks suspicious, let’s see if GRAF-pop (another method for inferring ancestry based on a different model with selected “ancestry-informative markers”) agrees:

assign_ancestry <- function(graf_pop){
    ancestry <- rep("",nrow(graf_pop))
    afr_idx <- graf_pop$`F(%)` >= 95
    eur_idx <- graf_pop$`E(%)` >= 87
    eas_idx <- graf_pop$`A(%)` >= 95
    afr_am_idx <- (graf_pop$`F(%)` < 95) & (graf_pop$`F(%)` >= 40) & (graf_pop$`A(%)` < 13)
    lat_am_1_idx <- (graf_pop$`F(%)` < 40) &( graf_pop$`E(%)` < 87) & (graf_pop$`A(%)` < 13) & (graf_pop$`F(%)` >= graf_pop$`A(%)`)
    three_pop <- (graf_pop$`A(%)` < 95) & (graf_pop$`E(%)` < 87) & (graf_pop$`F(%)` < 13) & (graf_pop$`F(%)` < graf_pop$`A(%)`)
    pac_idx <- three_pop & (graf_pop$GD1 > (30 * graf_pop$GD4^2 + 1.73))
    sas_idx <- three_pop & (graf_pop$GD4 > ((5 * (graf_pop$GD1 - 1.69)^2) + 0.042))
    lat_am_2_idx <- three_pop & (graf_pop$GD4 < 0) & !pac_idx
    other_idx <- (graf_pop$`A(%)` >= 13) & (graf_pop$`F(%)` >= 13)
    ancestry[afr_idx] <- "AFR"
    ancestry[eur_idx] <- "EUR"
    ancestry[eas_idx] <- "EAS"
    ancestry[afr_am_idx] <- "AFR_AM"
    ancestry[lat_am_1_idx] <- "LAT_AM_1"
    ancestry[pac_idx] <- "PAC"
    ancestry[sas_idx] <- "SAS"
    ancestry[lat_am_2_idx] <- "LAT_AM_2"
    ancestry[other_idx] <- "OTHER"
    ancestry[ancestry == ""] <- "OTHER"
    return(ancestry)
}
